class Solution {
    public String removeOccurrences(String s, String part) {
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(s);
        int m = part.length();
        if (m == 0) return s;
        while (true) {
            int idx = sb.indexOf(part);
            if (idx == -1) break;
            sb.delete(idx, idx + m);
        }
        return sb.toString();
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n * k) where n is the length of s and k is the length of part
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses a StringBuilder to repeatedly find and delete the leftmost occurrence of part until none remain. Leverages built-in indexOf and delete for concise, efficient in-place modification.

